Last week at my day job we had a major email incident. None of our email customers could send email while being off network. Meaning if they sent an email on their phone or tablet on a cellular network or another network the SMTP would get blocked. I believe my predecessor incorrectly set up email and anti spam by using the email security gateway also the SMTP gateway. This error only came to light as I believe we were originally running in a “bugged” state. This is good in an enterprise scenario as it protects employee emails. It is bad in a service provider’s scenario as you might imagine why. The executives want email working “now” but in that above configuration it is impossible. To fix it I had to do the unthinkable and trust every known IP in the world or 0.0.0.0/1. Email works off network and CEO is happy. They just do not understand the stress this will cause me in prevent the world from using our “email security gateway” as an open relay. I am a little different than most others as I use gaming as my stress reliever. To me it is the ultimate escape from reality and the stresses from my day job as a network administrator. Gaming allows me to explore worlds that I only read about in fiction books. It helps refresh my brain for another stressful day.
